\n==Trivia==\n* Scolipede is the [[List of Pokémon by height|tallest]] of all {{type|Bug}} Pokémon, as well as being the [[List of Pokémon by weight|heaviest]] {{type|Poison}} Pokémon.\n* Scolipede represents {{wp|November}} in the [[Unova]] [[horoscope]].\n\n===Origin===\n{{Bulbanews|On the Origin of Species: Venipede, Whirlipede and Scolipede}}\nScolipede\'s species shows that it was inspired by the {{wp|centipede}}, most likely the \'\'{{wp|Scolopendra gigantea}}\'\'. It could be based on \'\'{{wp|Arthropleura}}\'\', a prehistoric relative of centipedes that grew to two and a half meters. Scolipede also has a little in common with {{wp|millipede}}s, and may also draw inspiration from a red \'\'{{wp|Archispirostreptus gigas}}\'\', a species of millipede often kept as a pet.\n\n====Name origin====\nScolipede is a combination of \'\'{{wp|Scolopendra}}\'\' (genus of {{wp|centipede}}s) and \'\'centipede\'\' or \'\'millipede\'\'. \'\'Skolo-\'\' is an {{wp|Ancient Greek}} principle part meaning "pointed" or "impaling".\n\nPendror is derived from \'\'Scolopendra\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Bug|type2=Poison\n|ja=ペンドラー \'\'Pendror\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|Scolopendra}}\'\'\n|de=Cerapendra|demeaning=Possibly from {{tt|\'\'keras\'\'|Greek for \'horn\'}} and \'\'{{wp|Scolopendra}}\'\'\n|fr=Brutapode|frmeaning=From \'\'brute\'\' and \'\'{{wp|arthropod}}\'\'\n|es=Scolipede|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Scolipede|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=펜드라 \'\'Pendror\'\'|komeaning=From \'\'Scolopendra\'\'\n|zh_cmn=蜈蚣王 \'\'Wúgōngwáng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|蜈蚣 \'\'wúgōng\'\'|centipede}} and {{tt|王 \'\'wáng\'\'|king}}\n|zh_yue=蜈蚣王 \'\'Nghgūngwòhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|蜈蚣 \'\'nghgūng\'\'|centipede}} and {{tt|王 \'\'wòhng\'\'|king}}\n|ru=Сколипид \'\'Skolipid\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Poison}}\n{